@node "bloodbath" "Bloodbath"

BloodBath 
shoot-em-up with a lot of video animations in game, 
they run very smooth even with 68030.

@endnode


@node "darkforces" "Dark Forces"

Runs with a resolution of 320X200 VERY fast (040)!
Needs 68040 (runs also on 030 but is unplayable!)

-------
Dark Forces is fast on:
Amiga 3000, Cybervision 64, Cyberstorm 060 50MHz, 64MB FastRAM, 2MB ChipRAM
Amiga OS 3.1, Apple CD300 2xSpeed CD-ROM

@endnode


@node "descent" "Descent I/II"

Sorry, these games only run on PPC-machines!!!

@endnode


@node "doom" "Doom I/II"

MacDoom and MacDoom II run on my system.
But, to my surprise, even with an '060 they are slower than I had hoped.
Certainly playable in low-res, though.  Absolutely NO FUN on 030.

tested on Amiga 3000, Cybervision 64, Cyberstorm 060 50MHz, 64MB FastRAM, 
2MB ChipRAM, Apple CD300 2xSpeed CD-ROM

-------
Also runs on 040/25, 4XCD-ROM in low resolution

@endnode


@node "marathon" "Marathon I/II"

Marathon I/II
3D Dungeon textured games, slow of course, but it works.
Amiga 4000, 68030/68882, CyberVision 64,18Mb RAM, 4x NEC CDROM
Kick 3.0/WB 3.1

-------
Also runs on 040/25, 4XCD-ROM in low resolution

-------
A bit slow - but it works nonetheless on A1200/Blizzard 1230IV/
18MB RAM/OS3.0/4.4XCD-ROM from Pioneer

@endnode


@node "pathways" "Pathways Into Darkness"

Runs very fast
Also usable with 68030/25MHz

@endnode


@node "rebelassault" "Rebel Assault"

On 68030 you have to adjust the graphics-quality.
With 040 it runs with highest resolution.

@endnode


@node "shockwaveassault" "Shockwave Assault"

On 68030/25MHz it's unplayable!
On 040 with some gfx-adjustments.

@endnode


@node "superwingcommander" "Super Wing Commander"

Not tested, because it doesn't work with *my* CD-ROM drive

@endnode


@node "systemshock" "System Shock"

Sorry, this game only runs on PPC-machines!!!

@endnode


@node "wingcommander" "Wing Commander III/IV"

Sorry, Wing Commander III and IV only run on PPC-machines !!!

@endnode


@node "xwing" "X-Wing"

Needs 040.
You have to turn off very much gfx-details.
It really NEEDS a PPC...

@endnode


@node "daytentacle" "Day Of The Tentacle"

On 030/25MHz you will have to reduce the visible screensize.
On 040 you can enjoy the highest resolution.

@endnode


@node "deadalus" "The Deadalus Encounter"

Not tested, because it does not work on *my* machine.

@endnode


@node "dragonslair" "Dragon's Lair"

Dragon's Lair
Very fast at 320x240 12 fps
At 640x480 is slow (6 fps)
tested on A4000/040 36MHz 20MB RAM, Picasso II/CGfx

@endnode


@node "frankenstein" "Frankenstein - throug the eyes of the monster"

Not tested, because it does not work with *my* CD-ROM.
Please have a look at Q&A.

@endnode


@node "indianajones" "Indiana Jones IV"

Good playable with 030/25MHz (turn off smoothing!)
With 040 you can turn on smoothing (really good gfx)

@endnode


@node "myst" "Myst"

MYST runs very well on
A4000/030 25MHz  12MB-fast 2MB-chip =
CyberVision64, TandemCD controller with CD-ROM 
4x MITSUMI-ATAPI EIDE.

-------
Also runs on 040/25, 4XCD-ROM and on A4000 040 40MHz and
Cybervision64 (and a lot of memory, of course).

-------
Also successfully tested on: A1200/Blizzard 1230IV/18MB RAM/
OS3.0/4.4XCD-ROM from Pioneer

@endnode


@node "sammax" "Sam & Max"

On 030/25MHz too slow.
With 040 good playable.

@endnode


@node "spaceshipwarlock" "Spaceship Warlock"

Fast enough on 030/25MHz

@endnode


@node "ultrapinball" "3D Ultra Pinball"

3D Ultra Pinball 
Pinball Simulator like Pinball Fantasies on the amiga, but raytraced and you
play with a 3D view. Works ok on:
Amiga 4000, 68030/68882, CyberVision 64,18Mb RAM, 4x NEC CDROM
Kick 3.0/WB 3.1

@endnode


@node "a10" "A10 Attack"

A10 Attack 
runs fast.  A bit sluggish on 030.  Came on CD.
Tested on: Amiga 3000, Cybervision 64, Cyberstorm 060 50MHz, 
64MB FastRAM, 2MB ChipRAM, Apple CD300 2xSpeed CD-ROM

@endnode


@node "caliburn" "Crystal Caliburn"

Very good playable on 030/25MHz
No difference on 040

@endnode


@node "hornet" "F/A-18 Hornet"

With 030/25MHz you will have to reduce the displaysize
and number of objects

With 040 good playable in 640X480 at highest detail-level.

@endnode


@node "flightunlimited" "Flight Unlimited"

Sorry, this game only works on PPC-machines.

@endnode


@node "wolfpack" "Wolfpack"

Good on 030/25MHz.

@endnode


@node "tourgolf" "PGA Tour Golf"

Runs fast enough on 030/25MHz and 040.

@endnode


@node "tourgolfiii" "PGA Tour Golf III"

Way too slow even on 040.
But very good graphics-quality!!!

@endnode


@node "internationaltennis" "International Tennis"

International Tennis
Runs smoothly on A4000/040 36MHz 20MB RAM, Picasso II/CGfx

@endnode


@node "warcraft" "Warcraft"

Warcraft
Playable, a little slow, but the game is a lot of fun on
Amiga 4000, 68030/68882, CyberVision 64,18Mb RAM, 4x NEC CDROM

@endnode


@node "warlords" "Warlords"

WarLords II
Pretty good follow-up to WarLords (which existed on Amiga)
tested on Amiga 4000, 68030/68882, CyberVision 64,18Mb RAM, 4x NEC CDROM
Kick 3.0/WB 3.1

OK if you're patient.

Runs fast enough (what surprise ;-) on
Amiga 3000, Cybervision 64, Cyberstorm 060 50MHz, 64MB FastRAM, 2MB ChipRAM
Apple CD300 2xSpeed CD-ROM

@endnode


@node "simcity" "Sim City 2000"

SimCity 2000 runs fast.  Ok on 030 if you're patient.
Tested on: Amiga 3000, Cybervision 64, Cyberstorm 060 50MHz, 64MB FastRAM, 
2MB ChipRAM, Apple CD300 2xSpeed CD-ROM

-------
Requires 256 colours - a big strain on AGA :-)
Runs on: Amiga 1200/030MMU, 2Mb CHIP, 4Mb FAST, 2Mb PCMCIA, ~3Mb RAM for SS

-------
Much faster than the Amiga version on: A1200/Blizzard 1230IV/18MB RAM/
OS3.0/4.4XCD-ROM from Pioneer

@endnode


@node "simtower" "Sim Tower"

Sim Tower works on A1200/Blizzard 1230IV/18MB RAM/
OS3.0/4.4XCD-ROM from Pioneer

@endnode


@node "themepark" "Theme Park"

Theme Park
Just a bit slow (but you can play the Amiga version)
on A4000/040 36MHz 20MB RAM, Picasso II/CGfx

@endnode


@node "realmz" "Realmz"

Realmz
Nice gfx, a little slow again, but a lot of fun in this game
on Amiga 4000, 68030/68882, CyberVision 64,18Mb RAM, 4x NEC CDROM
Kick 3.0/WB 3.1

@endnode


@node "aladdin" "Aladdin Activity Centre"

Aladdin Activity Centre can occasionally crash on
A1200/Blizzard 1230IV/18MB RAM/OS3.0/4.4XCD-ROM from Pioneer
but could be an extension clash...

@endnode


